# ESP32-S3 Automated Water Top-Off System

Embedded system for automated aquarium water level management. Built on Waveshare ESP32-S3-Pico with PlatformIO/Arduino framework. Features single float sensor with fixed-dose pumping algorithm and EMA rate tracking, kalkwasser scheduler (mixing + peristaltic pump), audio alerts via DFPlayer Mini, status LED, web dashboard, and encrypted credential storage in FRAM.

## Hardware

**Platform:** Waveshare ESP32-S3-Pico (ESP32-S3, dual-core, WiFi, 16MB flash)

**Sensors and I/O:**
- 1x main float sensor (INPUT_PULLUP, active LOW, GPIO15) — water level detection with 1s debounce
- 1x reservoir float sensor (INPUT_PULLUP, active LOW, GPIO13) — monitors source water container level
- 1x ATO pump relay output (active LOW, GPIO11) — controls 12V dosing pump
- 1x mixing pump relay output (active LOW, GPIO12) — kalkwasser stirrer
- 1x peristaltic pump driver (LEDC/STEP, GPIO18) — kalkwasser dosing via TMC2209
- 1x status LED (GPIO16) — priority-based blink patterns (see below)
- 1x button input (INPUT_PULLUP, active LOW, GPIO14) — short press: provisioning / hold 5s: enter provisioning mode

**Audio:**
- DFPlayer Mini (UART1 TX-only, GPIO4) — plays alert sounds and voice feedback. TX-only mode: no ACK, repeat controlled by timer.

**Peripherals (I2C bus, SDA=GPIO6, SCL=GPIO7):**
- DS3231 RTC — hardware clock with battery backup, NTP-synchronized, UTC storage; falls back to ESP32 system time if absent
- FRAM 32KB (MB85RC256V at 0x50) — non-volatile storage for credentials (AES-256 encrypted), pump cycle history (ring buffer 60 records), EMA state, algorithm and kalkwasser config

**Time management:** RTC stores UTC. Display times auto-converted to local timezone (Poland CET/CEST with automatic DST). NTP sync at boot via IP addresses (DNS-independent).

## Status LED

Non-blocking priority-based state machine, updated every 100ms:

| Pattern | State |
|---------|-------|
| 3× flash 100ms, 2s pause | ERROR — intervention required |
| Solid on | Any pump active (ATO, mixing, or peristaltic) |
| 2× flash every 3s | Service Mode |
| Fast 200ms blink | WiFi connecting (boot phase) |
| Single 100ms pulse every 3s | Auto Mode, WiFi connected |
| Pulse every 3s, every 3rd = 3× fast blink | Auto Mode, no WiFi |

## Operating Modes

**Service Mode** (boot default) — all pumps and scheduler suspended. Manual pump operations work normally. Auto-switches to Auto Mode after 15 minutes.

**Auto Mode** — full operation: ATO algorithm active, kalkwasser scheduler running.

Toggle via web dashboard or automatic 15-minute boot timer.

## ATO Algorithm

State machine delivering a fixed, configurable dose of water each time the float sensor detects a water level drop. A rolling EMA tracks consumption rate (ml/h) and its deviation to generate dynamic alerts.

### State Flow

```
STATE_IDLE
    |  float sensor triggers debounce
    v
STATE_DEBOUNCING  (1s, 5 samples)
    |  debounce complete
    v
STATE_PUMPING     pump runs for: dose_ml / volumePerSecond seconds
    |  pump stops automatically
    v
STATE_LOGGING     save TopOffRecord + EmaBlock to FRAM
    |
    v
STATE_IDLE

Any state → STATE_ERROR when:
  - rolling 24h volume >= daily_limit_ml
  - rate deviation >= red alert threshold (after bootstrap)
  - reservoir sensor critical (4 consecutive low events)
STATE_ERROR requires explicit Cycle Reset (web button)
```

### EMA Rate Tracking

After each cycle:
- **rate** [ml/h] = `dose_ml / interval_since_last_cycle × 3600`
- **ema_rate_ml_h** — EMA of rate (alpha=0.20 default)
- **ema_dev_ml_h** — EMA of absolute deviations — dynamic alert threshold basis

Alert thresholds expressed as sigma multiples:
```
dev_sigma = (rate - ema_rate) / ema_dev × 100

|dev_sigma| >= yellow_sigma (default 10%) → yellow warning in GUI
|dev_sigma| >= red_sigma    (default 80%) → ERROR state (requires reset)
```

Alerts inactive during first 3 cycles (bootstrap period).

## Kalkwasser Scheduler

Independent scheduler running alongside the ATO algorithm.

- **Mixing:** 4× daily at 00:15, 06:15, 12:15, 18:15 local time — 5 min run + 1h settle window
- **Dosing:** 16× daily (every full hour except mix windows) — peristaltic pump via TMC2209 LEDC
- **Concurrency:** waits up to 10 min for ATO cycle to finish; skips slot if timeout
- **Persistence:** ON/OFF state stored in FRAM — survives restart, power cycle, and Cycle Reset

## Safety

- **Daily volume limit** (`daily_limit_ml`, default 2000 ml) — rolling 24h window; exceeding → ERROR
- **Reservoir sensor** — 4 consecutive low-water events → ERROR (prevents dosing into empty reservoir)
- **Midnight auto-restart** — firmware restarts at 00:00 local time daily; all pumps stopped safely before restart
- **Service Mode at boot** — 15-minute grace period before auto-operation begins

## Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| Platform | PlatformIO, Arduino framework |
| MCU | ESP32-S3 (Waveshare ESP32-S3-Pico) |
| Web server | ESPAsyncWebServer + AsyncTCP (mathieucarbou forks) |
| JSON | ArduinoJson 7.x |
| RTC | RTClib (Adafruit) — DS3231 |
| Storage | Adafruit FRAM I2C |
| Audio | DFRobot DFPlayer Mini (TX-only, UART1) |
| Encryption | mbedtls (AES-256-CBC, SHA-256) — bundled with ESP-IDF |
| Auth | SHA-256 password hash, random session tokens, HttpOnly cookies |

## Security

**Session authentication** — Login via password (SHA-256 hashed, stored in FRAM). Sessions are token-based, bound to client IP, HttpOnly cookie, max 10 sessions / 3 per IP.

**Rate limiting** — Max 5 requests/second per IP. After 10 failed login attempts, IP blocked for 60 seconds.

**Credential storage** — WiFi SSID/password, admin password hash, device ID stored in FRAM encrypted with AES-256-CBC. Configured via Captive Portal.

### Known Limitations

- HTTP only (no TLS) — traffic visible on LAN.
- Session tokens generated with `random()` — limited entropy on ESP32.
- No CSRF protection on POST endpoints.

## API Reference

All `/api/*` endpoints require session authentication (cookie `session`). Exception: `/api/health`.

### Authentication

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/login` | Authenticate (`password` form param) → set session cookie |
| POST | `/api/logout` | Destroy session |

### Status

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/status` | Full system status JSON |
| GET | `/api/health` | Lightweight health check, no auth required |

### System Control

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/system-toggle` | Toggle Auto Mode / Service Mode |
| POST | `/api/system-reset` | Reset ATO state machine to IDLE, clear ERROR |

### Pump Control

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/pump/direct-on` | Manual ATO pump on (bypasses algorithm) |
| POST | `/api/pump/direct-off` | Stop manual ATO pump |
| POST | `/api/pump/stop` | Emergency stop |
| GET/POST | `/api/pump-settings` | Get/set pump calibration (`flow_rate`, `volume_per_second`) |

### ATO Configuration

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/fill-water-max` | Get `dose_ml` and `daily_limit_ml` |
| POST | `/api/set-fill-water-max` | Set daily volume limit |
| POST | `/api/set-dose` | Set single dose volume |
| GET | `/api/daily-volume` | Rolling 24h stats |
| POST | `/api/reset-daily-volume` | Reset 24h counter |

### History and Statistics

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/cycle-history` | Ring buffer — 60 records, newest first |
| POST | `/api/clear-cycle-history` | Clear ring buffer |
| GET | `/api/get-statistics` | Error counters |
| POST | `/api/reset-statistics` | Reset error counters |

### Kalkwasser

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET/POST | `/api/kalkwasser-config` | Get/set config (`enabled`, `daily_dose_ml`) |
| POST | `/api/kalkwasser-calibrate` | Start/stop 30s calibration run |
| POST | `/api/kalkwasser-flow-rate` | Save measured ml from calibration run |

## Build and Deploy

Requires [PlatformIO](https://platformio.org/).

```bash
# Build and upload
pio run -e seeed_xiao_esp32s3 -t upload

# Serial monitor (115200 baud)
pio device monitor

# Build only
pio run -e seeed_xiao_esp32s3

# Clean build
pio run -e seeed_xiao_esp32s3 -t clean
```

## Provisioning (First-Time Setup)

1. **Enter provisioning mode** — Hold button (GPIO14) for 5+ seconds during boot. Audio feedback confirms.

2. **Connect to AP:**
   - SSID: `ESP32-WATER-SETUP`
   - Password: `setup12345`
   - IP: `192.168.4.1` (captive portal redirects automatically)

3. **Configure** — Enter device name, WiFi credentials, admin password.

4. **Reboot** — ESP32 restarts in production mode, loads credentials from FRAM, connects to configured WiFi.

Credentials are AES-256 encrypted before writing to FRAM. To reconfigure, repeat provisioning.

## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Check |
|---|---|
| FRAM not detected at boot | I2C wiring (SDA=GPIO6, SCL=GPIO7), 3.3V power, pull-up resistors on SDA/SCL; short circuit on I2C lines |
| WiFi not connecting | Re-run provisioning, verify SSID/password in Captive Portal |
| RTC battery warning | Replace CR2032 in DS3231 module |
| Auth fails after FRAM wipe | Re-run provisioning — credentials stored only in FRAM |
| Pump runs but no water | Check tube connections, pump direction, run calibration |
| STATUS_LED: 3× flash pattern | ERROR state — daily limit, red alert, or empty reservoir. Resolve cause, press Cycle Reset in GUI |
| Pump timing wrong | Calibrate: run manual pump 60s, measure ml output, set `volume_per_second = ml/60` in GUI |
| Kalkwasser slot skipped | ATO cycle running at slot time — kalkwasser waits max 10 min; reduce ATO dose or adjust schedule |

## Source Structure

```
src/
  main.cpp                  Entry point, mode detection, main loop
  algorithm/
    water_algorithm.*       ATO state machine, EMA tracking
    kalkwasser_scheduler.*  Mixing + peristaltic pump scheduler
    algorithm_config.h      Constants, data structures (TopOffRecord, EmaBlock, TopOffConfig)
  config/                   Settings, system enable/disable, FRAM credential loading
  core/                     Logging utilities
  crypto/                   AES-256 encryption for FRAM credentials
  hardware/
    fram_controller.*       FRAM memory management, ring buffer, all persistent data
    hardware_pins.h         GPIO pin definitions
    pump_controller.*       ATO pump relay control
    mixing_pump.*           Mixing pump relay control
    peristaltic_pump.*      Peristaltic pump via TMC2209 LEDC
    rtc_controller.*        DS3231 RTC + NTP sync + internal fallback
    water_sensors.*         Float sensor debouncing
    audio_player.*          DFPlayer Mini TX-only audio
    status_led.*            Priority-based status LED patterns
  network/                  WiFi manager
  provisioning/             Captive portal: AP, web server, button detection
  security/                 Auth manager, session manager, rate limiter
  web/                      Production web server, API handlers, HTML dashboard
```

## FRAM Memory Layout

```
0x0000–0x0017   Magic number and firmware version
0x0018–0x0417   Encrypted credentials (WiFi, admin password hash, device ID)
0x0500+         Water system data:
  0x0560–0x0575   TopOffConfig (20 bytes + 2B checksum, magic 0xA7)
  0x0580–0x0591   EmaBlock (16 bytes + 2B checksum)
  0x0610–0x0AC0   Ring buffer (60 × TopOffRecord, 20 bytes each)
  0x0AC0–0x0AD5   KalkwasserConfig (20 bytes + 2B checksum, magic 0xCA)
```
